div1.p: Territory of Washington Third Judicial District } ss. No.4704
To the Seriff of Pierce County, Greeting:

WHEREAS, C.H. Hutchinson recovered judgment against W.H. Harris in the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, on the 13th day of November A.D. 1885 for the sum of Dollars, with interest at the rate of until paid, and cost of suit, amounting to Seventeen and 40/100 ($17.40) Dollars. and Increased cost taxed at Jan and 75/100 ($10. 45/100) dollars. THEREFORE, in the name of the United States of America, you are hereby commanded forthwith to levy upon, seize and take into execution, the personal property of the said W.H. Harris in your County, sufficient subject to execution to satisfy said judgment, interest and increaed interest, cost and increased cost, and make sale therof according to law; and if sufficient perosnal property cannot be found, then you are further commanded to make the amount of saif judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, out of his real property, not exempt by law, and make retun of this writ within sixty days drom the date herof.
Hereiin fail not and have you then and there this writ

WITNESS the Hon. Roger S. Greene, Chief of Justice of the Supreme Court, and Judge of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, and the Seal of said Court, this 3rd day of December A.D. 1885
By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
Settled in full Jan, 22.00 1886 Leve's Boyd, Sheriff of Paves Co
Re & Due with 1885 Regerd Sheriff perco Co. No.4704
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, THIRD JUDICIAL DISTRICT
In Re, the petition of G.W. Hutchinson VS. for Writ of Habeas Corppus
Judgment for $ Interest at per cent, $ Increased Interest, $ Cost, $17.40 Clerk's Incresed Cpst $ 3.40 Sherif's Increased Costs of King County $7.35 Service 1.00 imlege 10.00 1.00 30 30.45
